<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 2:59AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Comanche, southeastern Jackson, southern Kiowa and Tillman Counties
through 330 AM CDT...
At 259 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Frederick, moving east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Frederick, Grandfield, Tipton, Chattanooga, Indiahoma, Davidson,
Manitou, Hollister, Loveland, Hess and southern Wichita Mountains
Wildlife Refuge.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
